The Sparky distribution containing this README file has a directory
called "manual".  Instructions for installing Sparky are in:

	manual/install.html

For an introduction to Sparky see:

	manual/index.html

For changes in recent Sparky versions see:

	manual/changelog.html

You can view the manual or get a copy of it or get the latest version
of Sparky from the web site:

	http://www.cgl.ucsf.edu/home/sparky

We have not written a paper describing Sparky.  If you publish work that
makes use of Sparky you can cite it as:

	T. D. Goddard and D. G. Kneller, SPARKY 3,
	University of California, San Francisco

If you cannot find answers to your questions, send email to

	sparky@cgl.ucsf.edu

The Sparky copyright, license and disclaimer is in the LICENSE file.
